Development of folkloristic research methods in the context of changing scientific paradigms will be analysed. The course focuses on the characteristics of Estonian folkloristics conditioned by the geographical and cultural location of Estonia as well as by its openness to dialogues with contradictory research traditions. The design of the research language, the special features of the research stages and the types of feedback are examined.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Observation of scholarly texts from three perspective: 1) method-centred analysis of the existing texts 2) composing texts and analysing of the academic language 3) presentation of research, compilation of feedbackLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) Skill to explain the formation of folkloristic research methods and scientific language, and interpret the academic texts from this perspective 2) Skill of analysing the different stages of a scientific work from the methodological/theoretical perspective 3) Ability to compile various feedback genres
